      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The data on resource strain is nuanced, with studies showing mixed results depending on how the strain is measured and the integration level of immigrants. While some localized pressure can occur, large-scale economic studies often demonstrate immigrants contribute positively to tax bases, offsetting costs. The \"concerns\" are often amplified by political rhetoric, but empirical evidence shows the net financial impact is not inherently negative for the whole economy.",
      "source": "target",
